Chapter 2: What Can We Pool?
Core Question
What can small regular contributions make possible?
Understand
Pooling is the engine.
A society does not wait for large wealth to begin.
It begins with rhythm.
Dues, pledges, savings circles, emergency funds, buying clubs, and opportunity funds all teach the same discipline:
We contribute regularly.
We keep records.
We decide together.
We protect privacy.
We report honestly.
Small money teaches large money how to behave.
A group that cannot manage $500 clearly should not rush to manage $50,000.
Pooling is not only financial.
A society can pool:
Money
 Time
 Skills
 Tools
 Vehicles
 Rooms
 Professional knowledge
 Contacts
 Childcare hours
 Meals
 Transportation
 Preparedness supplies
 Business referrals
 Youth mentoring
 Cultural labor
The question is not only:
How much money do we have?
The question is:
What can we reliably pool?
Discuss
