What moved, what stayed, what grew, and what should happen next?
Understand
The Wealth Circulation Report turns economic activity into shared memory.
It should show:
What money moved
 Where it went
 What it built
 What stayed local
 What supported members
 What supported businesses
 What trained youth
 What strengthened reserves
 What created opportunity
 What needs repair
 What should happen next
A truthful report is better than a dramatic claim.
Do not say “we built wealth” if you only spent money.
Say what actually happened.
Maybe you created the first buying club.
Maybe you supported two businesses.
Maybe you trained three youth in bookkeeping.
Maybe you built a $500 reserve.
Maybe you reduced emergency pressure.
Maybe you learned your ledger categories were weak.
That is evidence.
Evidence lets the society improve.
