Final question:
Can money, skill, labor, attention, and opportunity move through the society with memory, protection, and purpose?

Closing Principle
A society does not become wealthy because money passes through its hands.
It becomes stronger when money moves through trust, records, care, production, reinvestment, and protection.
Wealth circulation is not random spending.
It is organized movement.
It is the difference between a dollar that disappears and a dollar that teaches the community how to build.
Pool what is small.
Record what moves.
Route what repeats.
Support what serves.
Produce what is needed.
Reinvest what grows.
Protect what is vulnerable.
Report what happened.
Wealth circulates before it accumulates.

